&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join Bird’s mission to change the way the world moves, one ride at a time, by ensuring our award-winning electric vehicle fleet in Windsor is in peak condition. As a hands-on Vehicle Mechanic, you will repair and maintain our electric fleet and support warehouse operations to reduce carbon emissions and traffic. You will work with a motivated, tight-knit team to ensure every vehicle is safe and ready for the road.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute Vehicle Repairs: Diagnose and repair electric scooters and bikes, ranging from quick mechanical fixes to full vehicle refurbishments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Warehouse Efficiency: Maintain an organized workspace by moving scooters and managing parts inventory to support flow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain Safety Standards: Follow strict safety protocols while using hand tools and operating in a warehouse environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on Technical Learnings: Communicate roadblocks and repair insights to the team and supervisors to improve fleet health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Logistics Operations: Assist with fleet staging and prepare vehicles for deployment by the operations team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize Digital Tools: Use smartphone applications and internal software to track repair status and inventory usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in maintenance, logistics, or warehousing is preferred; mechanics, apprentices, or students are encouraged to apply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with hand tools and comfort using smartphone apps in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, time management, and problem-solving skills with a quick-learning mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift up to 50 lbs and remain on your feet for up to 8 hours.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have weekend availability and a flexible attitude toward seasonal shift changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
