&lt;p&gt;Morning Operations Specialist (Driver) – New York City, NY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bird launched micromobility. Now we’re shaping its future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re Bird, and we’re on a mission to transform the way the world moves—one ride at a time. Our products, services, and people share one goal: making cities more livable by enabling clean, accessible transportation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bird is a global leader in micromobility, providing affordable, on-demand transportation in over 200 cities worldwide. We partner closely with cities to deliver safe, sustainable alternatives to cars and reduce congestion and emissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a dependable Overnight Operations Specialist (Driver) to support fleet operations across New York City.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll drive a company van throughout NYC during overnight hours, repositioning e-scooters/e-bikes, swapping batteries, and ensuring vehicles are safe, charged, and ready for riders by morning. This role is ideal for someone who is self-motivated, comfortable working independently at night, and confident navigating city streets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Morning: 8:30 AM – 5 PM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two consecutive days off each week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely operate a company vehicle using app-based routing across NYC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Load, unload, and transport scooters and e-bikes (50–90 lbs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rebalance fleet from low-demand to high-demand areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Swap batteries and ensure all devices are properly charged&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform basic diagnostics and flag damaged or malfunctioning vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean, disinfect, and prepare vehicles for daily rider use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stage and organize vehicles in warehouse locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct routine checks on company vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team members via mobile apps and in-person communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with testing and quality assurance for new product features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$18.00 – $21.00 per hour, depending on experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must Have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driver’s license with a clean driving record&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2 years of driving experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable driving a cargo van in NYC (tight streets, traffic, night conditions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift up to 80–90 lbs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working overnight shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong time management and ability to work independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smartphone proficiency (app-based navigation and task management)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic English communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Highly Desired:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience driving larger vehicles (cargo vans, box trucks, U-Hauls)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with NYC streets, boroughs, and traffic patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in delivery, logistics, warehouse, or rideshare work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mechanically inclined (basic troubleshooting/maintenance)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
